    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-07-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="175"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.5764/1</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Hungary</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Brentano</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Budapest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-07-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1925</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received August 3.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 680</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the Department’s instruction
                    No. 940 of April 21, 1925,<note n="65" xml:id="d175fn65">See footnote 41, <ref
                            target="#pg_227">p. 227</ref>.</note> concerning agents of the Customs
                    Division of the United States Treasury stationed abroad being regularly and
                    officially attached to American Diplomatic Missions, I have the honor to
                    transmit a copy of a note from the Foreign Office dated July 8, 1925.<note
                        n="66" xml:id="d175fn66">Not printed.</note> received yesterday, stating
                    that Mr. James F. O’Neill, Customs Attaché, is placed on the Hungarian
                    diplomatic list. Mr. O’Neill has been informed of this action.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore Brentano</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
